Architecture plan for Issue #51: Add a colorful app background to the design system

Current project shape
- Backend: Rust Axum API in `backend/`, with the root Cargo workspace managing backend crates.
- Frontend: React + Vite + TypeScript SPA in `frontend/`.
- Styling: Tailwind theme extension in `frontend/tailwind.config.js` and global CSS variables/base styles in `frontend/src/styles.css`.
- Layout surfaces: app shell in `frontend/src/components/layout/AppFrame.tsx`, shared UI components in `frontend/src/components/ui/`, mailbox views in `frontend/src/mail/`, and auth/login views in `frontend/src/auth/`.
- Tests: Playwright E2E coverage in `e2e/`, with npm scripts at the repo root and frontend package level.

Module structure and file organization
- Keep the background implementation in the frontend design system layer, not in individual feature views.
- Define shared app background tokens in `frontend/src/styles.css` using CSS custom properties for:
  - the light-mode colorful app gradient
  - the dark-mode muted colorful app gradient
  - near-neutral surfaces layered over the gradient
  - border and subtle shadow colors used by surfaces
- Expose existing CSS variables through Tailwind in `frontend/tailwind.config.js` where utility classes need semantic colors.
- Apply the global background at the root document/app level so login, auth loading, mailbox, compose, and reading states inherit it consistently.
- Keep folder sidebar, message list, reading pane, compose panel, login card, and repeated UI cards on soft neutral or translucent surfaces to preserve text contrast.

Shared types and contracts
- No backend API, database schema, auth flow, mail DTO, or server routing changes are needed.
- The shared contract for this issue is visual: frontend components should consume semantic theme tokens rather than hard-coded page backgrounds.
- Theme switching should continue to rely on the existing `data-theme` flow from `frontend/src/theme/`.

Dependencies between issues
- Issue #51 builds on the existing minimal/airy design system described in the issue scope.
- It is inherited by all frontend views because the background belongs to the app base and layout shell.
- There are no other implementation issues in this setup batch, so future work can treat this as a design-system foundation.

Key design decisions
- Use a restrained multi-stop colorful gradient so the app base is more expressive without competing with mail content.
- Use a darker, muted gradient variant for dark mode to avoid bright color bloom behind dark surfaces.
- Preserve the quiet sans-serif typography, generous whitespace, subtle dividers, and single accent color from the existing design.
- Prefer global tokens and small layout-surface adjustments over broad component rewrites.
- Verify with frontend build/lint and visual checks of login, mailbox, reading pane, compose panel, and dark mode.
